What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a tough class that is very demanding, but it is very rewarding when things start to click. There is a lot of homework everyday, which isn't ideal, but seems necessary to improve your skills.
The course has a high volume of work but grading is generally very fair and I felt like I learned a lot of Japanese this semester.
Great teaching continues from 110-120 though in a more laid-back atmosphere; the workload remains high for good reason, and if you're committed to the language, it'll be a good ride.
